observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:

Inventory Committee conducts the physical count of all properties of the Municipality and provides all the necessary details in the RPCPPE. Thereafter, submit updated RPCPPE to the Audit Team;

OIC-Municipal Accountant:

Trace the records of those PPE with lacking information;

Prepare journal entries for the incorrect recording of PPE as expenses, as well as the misclassified PPEs; and

Provide complete disclosure of PPE in the Notes to the Financial Statements as required in IPSAS 17.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the HRMO to:
Come up with a concrete policy guideline relative to the hiring and rehiring of JO personnel to establish a clear expectation and protect the rights of both the employees and the Municipality;
Provide Statement of Duties and Responsibilities of JO personnel to clearly identify their responsibilities and perform their duties efficiently;
Set a standard wage rate based on their qualifications and suitability for the job applied, subject to the Municipality’s financial capacity, and
Request the installation of biometrics system for JO personnel to properly monitor their DTRs.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive-

Ensure the timely implementation of the development projects by the Municipality’s Local Development Council through proper coordination with the Municipal Engineer, MPDC, and other offices involved; 

Require the Municipal Engineer and other concerned officials to expedite the implementation of the unimplemented projects;

Require the Municipal Engineer to submit data to the Municipal Accountant, for the computation and enforcement of liquidated damages for projects with delayed completion.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
General Services Officer to complete the listing of the LGU Properties and furnish the Report of Physical Count of PPE to the Municipal Accountant;
The Municipal Engineer to furnish the Mun. Accountant with all Statement of Works Accomplished (SWA) on all Infrastructure Assets monitored by their office;
Municipal Accountant Designate to extract all the PPE items from his earliest available records to aid him in the preparation of the PPE schedule, reconcile the data furnished by GSO and Mun. Engineer,  and set up depreciation expenses based on the established schedule;
Municipal Accountant Designate to make appropriate adjusting entries for deficiencies and errors noted in items A, B and C and as summarized on the table 2.1 shown in this finding; and,
Three officers mentioned above to coordinate with each other in establishing the data necessary to complete the PPE schedule of the LGU.

We recommend that Management require the: 

a. Municipal General Services Officer to submit a Report of the Physical Inventory of the Property, Plant and Equipment for the year 2017 and to maintain updated Property Cards as prescribed by Section 119 & 124 of COA Circular 2002-003;

b.Yearly conduct of physical count of PPE as mandated by law; 

c.Municipal Accountant to maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards, Real Property Ledger Cards as prescribed by Section 119, 120 of COA Circular 2002-003.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the :

a.	personnel concerned to meticulously plan the procurement of the projects funded out of the BUB/GPBP to ensure that they are implemented within the timelines;
 b.	Municipal Accountant to submit the Memorandum of Agreement ;
 c.	Install the community billboard for the BUB Funds downloaded and provide a picture;

